✨Just Listed 📍 9701 Cannon St., Villa Park - $3,845,000✨

4 Bed / 6 Bath / 4,968 Sq. Ft. / 26,625 Sq. Ft. Lot Size

Nestled within the prestigious Villa Park community, discover this newly built contemporary masterpiece designed for ultimate entertainment and luxury living. This two-story residence, bathed in natural light thanks to its soaring ceilings and open floor plan, offers a total of 4 bedrooms and 6 baths, as well as a spacious office. At the heart of this residence lies the chef’s kitchen, featuring an oversized quartz-topped island, a 60-inch range oven, and a Thermador oversized refrigerator. The main living area, designed for quintessential California indoor-outdoor living, welcomes the outdoors in with accordion sliding glass doors leading to a sprawling yard. The primary suite, with its floor-to-ceiling built-in closet storage and electric shades, connects effortlessly to the outdoor oasis. Here, you’ll find a saltwater pool, spa, an overflowing baja pool, three inviting firepits, a sunken seating area, and a fully equipped BBQ island with a fridge and sink. An astroturf side yard with batting cage/sports field and a basketball court complete this outdoor haven. Beyond the main residence, you will find a separate guest house spanning over 1,100 square feet with its own rooftop astroturf area and set of amenities. It boasts a fully equipped gym and an office/guest area, complete with a full kitchen and bath. The three-car garage is not only equipped with a large walk-in safe but also features an additional storage room and a 220-voltage electric car charger. Throughout the home, custom cabinets by Derrick Wayne and ceramic floors showcase intricate craftsmanship. Every corner exudes opulence, from the massive stone tub to the master sinks with a vanity, and the upscale plumbing fixtures. Additional features include two tankless gas water heaters, a robust 2-inch water line for excellent water pressure, and automatic blinds in the master suite and high windows. No detail has been spared in creating this haven of sophistication and comfort.

Looking to buy or sell? Let me help! 949.527.8281

✨Just Listed in Irvine 16 Prairie Grass, Shady Canyon - $5,995,000 ✨

 5 Beds / 6 Baths / 4,960 Sq. Ft. / 15,159 Lot Size 

Experience the epitome of old-world charm with the convenience of luxury modern-day living in this beautifully appointed and recently remodeled Spanish Revival villa. Nestled atop a large private lot with resort-like grounds, the home is located in the prestigious Villa Sycamore neighborhood of the exclusive gated community of Shady Canyon that features 16,000 acres of preserved rolling hills that cocoon the area from the outside world. Feel welcomed through the glazed Spanish tile and wrought-iron arched entry gate into the gorgeous front courtyard complete with a serene outdoor fountain. The open living/dining room in the center of the home showcases a double-height vaulted ceiling with exposed wood beams, a stunning fireplace and rows of French doors lining both sides of the room, providing a seamless transition between indoor/outdoor living. The spacious large yard that surrounds the entire estate includes multiple outdoor living areas with exterior fireplaces, a highly upgraded covered patio, outdoor televisions and lighting, a sparkling pool with elegant waterfall features, and a custom covered outdoor kitchen. Inside, the updated chef’s kitchen includes new state-of-the-art appliances including a built-in SubZero fridge, with additional fridge and freezer drawers in the butler’s pantry, a Wolf steam oven, and custom BlueStar commercial gas range/oven.The oversized primary suite is replete with a new built-in desk space, remote controlled fireplace, upholstered walls, a massive walk-in closet and a completely rebuilt luxurious spa-like bathroom with dual vanity sinks, radiant heated flooring, antique glass wall, and a built-in sauna. The additional four bedrooms with remodeled ensuite bathrooms complete the estate, including a private casita which can be used as either a fifth bedroom or office.

Just Listed in San Diego📍 5115 Gordon Ln., Pacific Beach - $7,000,000

5 Bed / 5.5 Bath / 5,179 Sq. Ft. 

Welcome to Vista de Los Altos, an unparalleled development nestled in the heart of San Diego, where 5115 Gordon Lane offers you a perfect blend of high-end features and intimate luxury. Your panoramic view of the bay and ocean are guaranteed for life, thanks to the city’s recorded landscape envelopes that ensure an unobstructed view. From the moment you step in, you’re greeted by an expansive entry warmed with incredible natural light and inviting views of the custom-tiled outdoor retreat and pool. Immediately become enamored with the airy floating staircase and impressive attention to detail. Lean into the peaceful symphony of nature and architecture co-existing effortlessly as the Japanese Red Maple tree grows through the deck, adding a delightful blend of natural wonder to your home. Equipped with a whole-house smart home system, including a speaker network, your residence becomes an epitome of technological refinement while seamless living is made easy powered by solar. The one-of-a-kind kitchen boasts top-of-the-line appliances for an ultra-modern touch to your gourmet kitchen. Designed with an emphasis on entertainment as well as intimacy, this house can seamlessly host a grand party of over 100, but also provide an inviting atmosphere for those oh-so-precious solitary moments throughout your day. Nestled within a private circle of 14 brand-new ocean-view lots, each home is a testament to exceptional craftsmanship. To live at 5115 Gordon Lane is to savor a unique lifestyle found nowhere else in San Diego. Discover your dream home and allow the arresting views, stunning design, and luxurious features to leave a mark on your soul. Come, cherish this remarkable abode, and let its story become a part of your own.

✨Just Sold - 2201 Bayside Dr. -
$24,500,000✨

5 Beds / 9 Baths / 9,129 Sq. Ft.
This newly constructed custom estate offers exclusive Corona Del Mar waterfront living with intricate design touches and a harmonious blend of natural stone and wood elements. Consisting of 5 ensuite bedrooms and 9 bathrooms and approximately 50 feet of private beachfront, it caters to water enthusiasts and offers shared ownership of one of the longest private docks on the west coast, capable of accommodating multiple yachts up to 100ft in length. Upon arrival, you will be greeted by meticulously landscaped surroundings, a grand pivot door, and a double height foyer that sets the tone for the residence. Inside, the space boasts European wide plank bleached oak flooring by Gaetano, illuminated floating staircases, and expansive glass features that fill the approximately 9,129 square feet of interiors with an abundance of natural light. The property seamlessly connects to its surroundings through slide-away pocket doors that open onto a heated patio, a zero-edge saltwater pool and spa, and a courtyard featuring a built-in Lynx Grill.
The kitchen features custom Honed Calcatta Vagli slab countertops and backsplash, a 55” La Canche designer stove imported from Paris, a butler’s pantry, and stained white oak cabinetry. Convenience is paramount, with a Waupaca elevator servicing all four floors, including the lower level, which encompasses a media area, a dry bar, and temperature controlled wine room. Upstairs, the owner’s suite presents a heated wraparound balcony with mesmerizing water views, a living space with a fireplace, and two spa-like bathrooms, each complemented by its own walk-in closet. The top level reveals a lounge area that opens onto a rooftop deck with grass and sweeping views of the Newport Beach Harbor offering limitless ocean-view entertaining. Equipped with cutting-edge technology, the property also includes a nearly 3,000 sa. ft., 6+ car garage with epoxy flooring. Expertly designed by Brandon Architects, Patterson Custom Homes, Harvard Investment Group, and Brooke Wagner Design.

✨Coming Soon in Malibu - 24844 Malibu Rd. - $53,000,000✨

An architectural tour de force and only one of the few private homes in the United States designed by the renowned Pritzker Prize-winning Japanese architect, Tadao Ando. Best known for his minimalist structures and his assured use of reinforced concrete, Ando’s trademark design of “smooth-as-silk” concrete is wholly present in the structure and surface of the home. Constructed of approximately 1,200 tons of concrete, 200 tons of steel reinforcement, and 12 massive pylons driven more than 60 feet into the sand with AD100 architecture firm Marmol Radziner acting as executive architect and general contractor, the structure is an everlasting beacon of permanence on California’s coastline. Natural light is used creatively throughout the space, another signature of Ando, to manipulate a warm feeling throughout the building and harmonize with its natural surroundings. The home spans +/- 4,000 sq. ft. of interior space and approximately 1,500 sq. ft. of outdoor decks with ocean views from every room. Currently all interior finishes have been removed from the property, and work is needed to either restore or reimagine the interiors. Thoughtfully located on the prestigious and quiet Malibu Road, with easy access and close proximity to the finest restaurants, shopping, and entertainment in all of Malibu. An exceedingly rare architectural achievement that should be seen as a masterful work of art, rather than just a residence.

Happy New Year and Merry Christmas May the festive season bring you joy, warmth, and wonderful moments with your loved ones. Wishing you a year ahead filled with happiness, success, and prosperity.
Cheers to new beginnings and joyful celebrations!

✨Just Listed in Manhattan Beach - 1001 1st St. - $29,900,000✨

6 Bed / 9 Bath / 9,479 Sq. Ft.

The most impressive and high-quality Contemporary estate ever built in Manhattan Beach, featuring panoramic ocean views from every room. After a laborious multi-year build, this approximately 9,500 sq. ft. showstopper seamlessly fuses glass, cedar, and concrete into a triumphant architectural tour de force with a sense of permanence and grandeur. Integral to the structure and aesthetic of the home, the scalloped concrete walls seen on the exterior and interior walls resemble an undulating wave-like texture accomplished by custom milled formwork which complement the surrounding Pacific landscape. Custom cedar clads the remaining walls and ceilings, bringing warmth and visual impact throughout the sleek space. Double-height ceilings and oversized automated Otiima pocketing doors and windows create a sense of expansion within, as the home seamlessly unfolds into an extensive beautifully landscaped outdoor terrace and pool/spa perfect for California living. An additional shaded patio with fireplace is created by the deep cedar overhangs from the upper floor and the roof. Generously nestled on an extra-wide corner lot, the home is replete with 6 bedrooms plus an additional office/nursery, 9 bathrooms, home theater, game room, wine cellar, wet bar, and gym, with architecture by Laney LA. Additional amenities include 48 solar panels with Tesla Powerwalls, elevator, 14 zone A/C technology platform system, Control4 home automation, and 3-car garage with additional driveway parking. An exceptionally rare opportunity to own a meticulously crafted beach estate with soul and sophistication.
